-- Embraer wins orders worth $1.7 billion
-- 
-- Mon Jun 20, 2011 5:53am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/06/20/us-airshow-embraer-orders-idUSTRE75J1Q220110620

 

 LE BOURGET, France  (Reuters) - Brazilian regional planemaker Embraer said it won orders for 39 Embraer 190 regional jets worth $1.7 billion at list prices at the Paris Air Show. 

 "We have seen a very good demand for our jets," Paulo Cesar de Souza e Silva, Embraer vice-president for commercial aviation, said on Monday. Customers include Air Lease Corp, Air Astana, General Electric, Sriwijaya Air and Kenya Airways, Embraer said. The planemaker predicted demand for 7,225 regional jets in the next 20 years, worth $320 billion. (Reporting by Cesar Bianconi; Editing by  James Regan )